Sample Code - 

Day 1 

Problem 1
Problem Statement - 
You are given an array of integers.
Your task is to find and return the smallest element present in the array.
Solution - 
int findSmallest(int[] arr){
int min = arr[];
for (int i=1; i<arr.length; i++){
     if(arr[i]<min){
        min = arr[i];
    }
  }
return min;
}

* Final Time Complexity - O(n)
* Final Space Complexity - O(1) (constant space)


Problem 2
Problem Statement - 
Find the sum of all elements in an array
Solution - 
int[] arr = {2,4,6,8};
int sum = 0;
for (int i=0; i<arr.length; i++){
     sum = sum + arr[i];
}
System.out.println(sum);








